g.text: Level 0: Original Study Data - Raw, unprocessed data with restricted access to Core Data Team only
Level 1: Consortium Shared Data - Processed data shared only among HE²AT Center Consortium partners with limited indirect identifiers
Level 2: RP1/RP2 De-identified Data - Retained by HE²AT Center for future attribution projects with ethics approval
Level 3: Inferential Data - Aggregated and anonymized data derived from analyses, available for open access
1. Data ownership remains with original providers
2. Cloud migration necessitated by NIH funding changes
3. Regional isolation prevents unlawful data transfer
4. Azure RBAC implements tiered access controls
5. Higher levels of data (2-3) retained by HE²ATCenter
6. Future attribution projects with ethics approval
7. All data usage governed by ethical approvals
